                    <state type="martyr" source="#bib1178-2">
                        <p>Martyr</p>
                    </state>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1178-2">AMS, IV, 166- 70 ; BHO, 180 et 1043.
Suhadii ', I, 345-48.
BS, II, 1284 (J.-M. Sauget).
Sur le christianisme au Gilan : J.M. Fiey, dans PdO 2 (1971), 329-38.</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1178">Brīkhīshōʿ and his ten companions were
          martyred in the time of Shapur; they emerged in the context of a battle.</note>
                    <event type="attestation" xml:id="attestation1178-1" source="#bib1178-2">
                        <p xml:lang="en">Brīkhīshōʿ is commemorated in <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/260">Zebinas, Lazarus, Maroutha, Narses, Elijah, Mahri, Habib, Saba, Berikhicho, Jonas et Chembaiteh (text)</title>.</p>
                    </event>
                    <event type="attestation" xml:id="attestation1178-2" source="#bib1178-2">
                        <p xml:lang="en">Brīkhīshōʿ is commemorated in <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/330">Berikhisho and ʿAbdisho (text)</title>.</p>
                    </event>
